---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="About | Binary Executioner">
  <section class="post">
    <header class="post-header">
      <p class="post-path">./about/profile.txt</p>
      <h1>About Binary Executioner</h1>
      <p class="post-description">
        Threat hunting, CTF writeups, cloud security notes, detection engineering,
        and the occasional rabbit hole that refused to die quietly.
      </p>
    </header>

    <div class="post-content">
      <h2>whoami</h2>

      <p>
        Hey, I’m Sidhartha — writing here as <strong>Binary Executioner</strong>.
        I work as a Threat Hunter and use this site as my public security notebook.
      </p>

      <p>
        Most of what I publish here comes from Hack The Box, TryHackMe, VulnLab,
        PwnedLabs, CyberDefenders, cloud labs, Windows/Linux practice, and detection
        engineering experiments.
      </p>

      <h2>What this site is</h2>

      <p>
        This is where I document writeups, attack paths, enumeration steps,
        privilege escalation notes, detection ideas, scripts, and lessons learned.
      </p>

      <blockquote>
        Breaking boxes. Building detections. Writing the notes I wish I had.
      </blockquote>

      <h2>Topics</h2>

      <ul>
        <li>CTF writeups and lab walkthroughs</li>
        <li>Cloud security and misconfiguration abuse</li>
        <li>Windows, Linux, and Active Directory notes</li>
        <li>Detection engineering and KQL ideas</li>
        <li>Malware analysis and security research notes</li>
        <li>Tools, scripts, and automation</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Disclaimer</h2>

      <p>
        Everything here is for educational and ethical security learning.
        I write about legal labs, intentionally vulnerable environments, and
        sanitized learning material.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>